% gen335: demonym knowledge — place → demonym for completion queries.
% KB-first: add a demonym/2 fact and "born in X, therefore I am a ___"
% resolves with zero C changes. The completion_chain/2 consumer in
% mod_knowledge reads the cue + predicate; the data is KB knowledge.
% ==================================================================

% completion_chain(Cue, ResultPred): when the user says "Cue X" and the
% sentence ends with a blank/article, query ResultPred(X, ?Y) and respond
% with Y. The C motor (mod_knowledge) reads this; the data grows here.
% gen335b: profession chain — "studied X, therefore I am a ___"
% study medicine → doctor, study law → lawyer, etc.

% ═══ Conoscenza di ordine superiore cresciuta sulla learning mesh (gen335) ═══════
% Vedi docs/plans/learning-mesh.md §4.4. Fatti QUI accanto ai loro parenti (is_a,
% answer_frame, capital_of_country) così il save-map instrada la crescita futura.
% Operatori (regole) in forma robusta: closure a predicato separato, right-recursive.

% -- Tassonomia + ereditarietà di proprietà/abilità (kind_of/prop_of/able_to) --

% -- Ordinamenti transitivi (comparativo + temperatura + temporale) --

% -- Geografia (continente) e paternità letteraria (rispondibili via answer_frame) --

% ── TAXONOMY + CATEGORIES + PROPERTIES + COMPARISONS + CAUSALITY + GEOGRAPHY + SUPERLATIVES (scattered from mesh-session.p0, gen335) ──

% ── DEFAULT REASONING with NAF (non-monotonic) ──
% "birds fly" with exceptions (gen335 round-2)

% ── HABITAT & DIET ──

% ── TEMPORAL PERIODS ──

% ── L4: ONTOLOGY OF RELATIONS (meta-knowledge about predicates) ──




% ── L7: QUESTION TYPOLOGY ──

% ── L8: ARGUMENTATION ──
% Socrates syllogism (classic example of deductive reasoning)
% ── PERIODIC TABLE (118 elements, gen335 round-3) ──
% ── COMPLETE WORLD GEOGRAPHY (gen335 round-3) ──
able_to($X, $A) :- has_own_ability($X, $A).
able_to($X, $A) :- kind_of($X, $Y), able_to($Y, $A).
activity_step(rainy_sunday, 1, "Choose one indoor activity that fits the weather, such as reading, cooking, or a quiet film").
activity_step(rainy_sunday, 2, "Make the room comfortable with warm light, a drink, and a clear place to sit").
activity_step(rainy_sunday, 3, "Do one small useful task first so the rest of the afternoon feels unhurried").
activity_step(rainy_sunday, 4, "Leave time for rest rather than packing the day with errands").
activity_summary(rainy_sunday, "I don't have real favorites, but on a rainy day I'd read quietly with a warm drink.").
activity_topic(rainy_sunday, afternoon).
activity_topic(rainy_sunday, rain).
activity_topic(rainy_sunday, rainy).
activity_topic(rainy_sunday, sunday).
after_in_time($X, $Z) :- after_in_time($X, $Y), after_in_time($Y, $Z).
